-- U.K. Miller Wheat Use Fell 0.8% in April From 2011, Defra Says
-- B y   W h i t n e y   M c F e r r o n
-- 2012-06-14T11:36:14Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-14/u-k-miller-wheat-use-fell-0-8-in-april-from-2011-defra-says.html
Wheat use by U.K. millers fell 0.8
percent in April from the same month a year earlier, the
Department of Environment, Food and Rural Affairs said.  Millers processed 468,100 metric tons of wheat in the
month, down from 471,800 tons in 2011, Defra said in a  report  on
its website today. Brewers, maltsters and distillers used 47,000
tons of wheat in April, down 13 percent from a year earlier,
according to the report.  To contact the reporter on this story:
